00:06:55.679 --> 00:06:57.679
Is that a security risk?

00:06:59.679 --> 00:07:00.679
So this is a demo.

00:07:00.679 --> 00:07:03.679
This is not a security risk for us in this very moment.

00:07:04.679 --> 00:07:10.679
It is best practice to be using a package called .env in the Python world.

00:07:10.679 --> 00:07:16.679
In the R world, it will automatically load from your environment when you make the board connect.

00:07:16.679 --> 00:07:26.679
But in Python, if you use that .env package, you can use a .env file and it will load in all of your environment variables.

00:07:26.679 --> 00:07:28.679
Then you don't have anything in plain text.

00:07:28.679 --> 00:07:32.679
And you can share your screen with others and they won't see your API keys.

00:07:33.679 --> 00:07:37.679
And .env is just like B-O-T-E-N-V?

00:07:37.679 --> 00:07:38.679
Yep.

00:07:39.679 --> 00:07:43.679
Kind of like the phonetic spelling of the period .env file.

00:07:43.679 --> 00:07:44.679
Okay.

00:07:44.679 --> 00:07:45.679
Awesome.

00:07:45.679 --> 00:07:46.679
Thank you.

