00:15:10.679 --> 00:15:13.679
There's a few different ways you can do this,

00:15:13.679 --> 00:15:14.679
especially with using Connect.

00:15:14.679 --> 00:15:18.679
So Connect has some built-in organization tools,

00:15:18.679 --> 00:15:22.679
including the ability to add labels to various pieces of content,

00:15:22.679 --> 00:15:23.679
including pins.

00:15:23.679 --> 00:15:26.679
So for example, if you had maybe of those a hundred plus pins,

00:15:26.679 --> 00:15:30.679
maybe you had five or 10 of them associated with a specific project,

00:15:30.679 --> 00:15:32.679
you can easily give those a label

00:15:32.679 --> 00:15:35.679
and search for them easily within the Connect instance.

00:15:35.679 --> 00:15:37.679
There's also other tools.

00:15:37.679 --> 00:15:40.679
Some of you may have heard of a tool called Connect Widgets,

00:15:40.679 --> 00:15:43.679
which allows you to take various pieces of content.

00:15:43.679 --> 00:15:44.679
It doesn't have to be a pin.

00:15:44.679 --> 00:15:47.679
It can be a pin, a Shiny app, a Korto, or a Markdown,

00:15:47.679 --> 00:15:49.679
and essentially create a single document

00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:51.679
that organizes all that content.

00:15:51.679 --> 00:15:53.679
So you'd certainly have options

00:15:53.679 --> 00:15:56.679
for organizing your content on the Connect instance,

00:15:56.679 --> 00:16:00.679
